abstract: Veterinarians at Washington National Zoo are surprised when they deliver twin giant panda cubs from mother Mei Xiang; global audience follows rare birth of healthy panda cubs online.
lead_paragraph: Mei Xiang, a giant panda at the National Zoo in Washington, gave birth to healthy twin cubs on Saturday, three days after the zoo’s staff discovered she was pregnant.

headline.main: Giant Panda Gives Birth to Two Cubs at the National Zoo
headline.print_headline: Surprise, Two Times Over: Giant Panda Gives Birth to Twins at the National Zoo
